{"build_type":"executable","description":"Trivial executable returning 7, used as the body of a thin PT_INTERP binary in the 3b-ii test. Its own code returns 7; the thin binary's PT_INTERP points at a separate interpreter that exits 42. Running the thin binary must exit 42 (the kernel invoked the interpreter) and NOT 7 (which would mean PT_INTERP was ignored) — a discriminating proof.","module_name":"return-integer-seven-value-inside-program","package_name":"return-integer-seven-value-inside-program","function_definitions":{"return-integer-seven-value-inside-program":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v7","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":7},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"v7"}}]}}}